Review: Tea and Cookies are worth of money, the sugar is kept seperate. The staff service is quick. They have wide varieties of snacks and pastries also. Its in the Bangalore International Terminal in between Gate No. 39 & 40.  Near to it there is lot of sitting space to relax and enjoy the break before flight.

This is one of the eateries in the ground level of Kempegowda International Airport, Bangalore.  They have snacks, bakery products and other dishes for breakfast, lunch and dinner.  The place is neat and elegant with less crowd.  Service is friendly.  I enjoyed filter coffee.
A small decent place for tea and snacks located on lower gates of airport.

Located inside the bangalore international airport, this food outlet is near to gate 3 and has to come down from the main terminal to be reached. It's a decent food outlet and mainly serves baked items, juices and other beverages. They have few seating table in front of the store too.
The food is of best quality. Very well behaved staffs. Remembering that you're in the airport the food is value for money! I'd recommend this place.

Those familiar with the layout of Bangalore International Airport, they would know that gates 3 to 11 are located on the ground floor, with an escalator. Urban food Market basically serves bakery items such as croissants, sandwiches, cookies etc. It also serves coffee. There is no difference in prices as compared to other similar joints, but it definitely offers convenience for fliers during their waiting time. One interesting thing is that it offers take-away, which is actually a substitute for costly on-board meals.

This is very near to Gate 40.  They have varieties of breads, cappuccino, latte and our indian filter coffee,.donuts. Pastries, Sandwich etc.  They also have all aerated drinks.  Good service by the staff. They also sell organic coffee powder.  Had vegetarian puff and coffee ans they were good.
I am really impressed with courtesy of the management. I had a problem with payment with my card they even told me you can go without paying if you have no option but some how I paid them.

Tried Cappuccino and Latte and both were upto the mark. Pricing was reasonable 125 Rs. given that it's in airport basement G1-G6. 

The croissants and burger were also well decorated and tasty but little over priced. 

All in all for good early morning kick.

This place is fit only for those who want to have a quick bite. Don't expect service or taste or fresh food.
I ordered crossiant.... Felt like eating... But could not eat. It was at least 3 days old. And has been reheated just before serving.
Not mention that food at airports is usually expensive.

Just try carrying ur own food if u feel hungry at the gates of any airport. :)
Puffs, Samosa, Sandwiches and Burgers. Good for a quick snack before a flight. They even have choices in non alcoholic beverages.
We had vegitable roll and burger in the airport.its really hot and spicy and it has made freshly as well as ever hour they are restocking..one of the fantastic food which I had in Bangalore Airport.
Good products available here

This place can be listed amongst the worst  places for food.

First time I tried a double barrel sausage treat and it was like a papad, next time I was hungry again and thought I will try brownie, atleast that can't go bad.... It was a disaster. When I asked the staff was rude enough to deny the truth that brownie was like a rock. It was like rusk with some walnuts on it. I think the pastry chef might have worked in a local biscuit factory before.... Even in airports no value for complaints, hence writing this review.

Reasonably good food outlet within kempagowda airport bengaluru. The food varieties are limited, mostly baked items and juices. Number of tables are few and could see the surroundings are super clean. I feel this is just an OK food outlet.

Ordered a hot chocolate worth RS 160. The quantity was less and well the hot chocolate was just some syrup with warm milk which tasted bland. Please do not go.
Even after paying premium price. You will get 2nd class food
Looks interesting.. but tastes bad. Disappointed
Bad experience nit good in food and service both

Not much options.

Very bad customer service. The person at the counter swallows what he's saying half way through. Also he was doing some other work while making us wait for some time before taking our order. Also they don't have half the items on the menu (no hot chocolate or caramel latte; had to settle for green tea).
Had a Paneer tikka Panini here, it was nice.....

I want to thank the waiter who gave me a replacement without charging when i dropped my muffin. That really lifted my mood a little bit.
I also left the water bottle there after paying, so please give it someone who isn't in good mood.
The muffin n coffee were good.

Not worth for trying. Either the food is that way or they serve it that way, very poor taste. Ordered a hot chocolate, it was made in bad form of taste.
Picked up a veg puff... It will put the Guntur chillies to shame ...Instead of being a veg puff it turned out to be a RED CHILLI puff, not palatable by any standards...V dissapointed...
Sandwich was full of tomatoes thinnest slice of old ham! It was yuck!

One of the worst paninis I have ever had in my life. They literally gave me a block of stale bread with two slices of ham and a single mutilated slice of cheese, which they microwaved until the last little drop of moisture was sucked out of â€¦
